comments.text:
Muslims are often confounded when Christians warn them that islam is clearly from satan. Besides the violent nature and impact of the revelations, the fact that mohammed admitted to reciting verses from the devil and having a devil-companion who did not "order" him to do anything but good, was bewitched for nearly a year, had several run-ins with jinns, and at one point physically wrestled with and choked satan. Or the fact that islam teaches the redemption of demons (fallen angels), that satan is omnipresent (able to touch every child, stay in every Muslim's nose, enter the mouth when a person yawns, etc.), superstitious beliefs and practices (killing a gecko with one strike to gain heaven points, using chants/spells for protection/healing, ritual baths), and the obvious glaring symbolism of the moon and star in honour of Hubal (the moon god of Medina and the Kaaba) and Venus/Al-Lat, gods venerated by the Quraysh.

But perhaps the most obvious red flag is the name of Jesus. In the Bible, it is written that:

- In My name (Jesus) shall they cast out devils (Mark 16:17).
- Many will prophesy in His name, cast out devils, and do many wonderful works in His name (Matthew 7:22).
- In His name shall the Gentiles trust (Matthew 12:21).
- Repentance and remission of sins should be preached in His name among all nations, beginning at Jerusalem (Luke 24:47).
- Through His name, whosoever believeth in Him shall receive remission of sins (Acts 10:43), and much more.

Is it merely a coincidence, then, that while all the prophets, including Paul, had their names properly transliterated in the Quran/Tafsirs, only Jesus was called by a bizarre, derogatory, and obscure name? Now, before you say that Isa is the same name and has the same meaning as Jesus, do some research. You'll probably end up claiming that Jesus was not His real name or that Christians lost/corrupted His real name. So make sure the evidence you provide in response surpasses the tens of thousands of manuscripts from Jewish/Roman historians, letters, Biblical commentaries from Church fathers, including Christian oral tradition, coins, art, rock inscriptions, and artefacts dating across the centuries, all explicitly bearing the name, Jesus.

Because, even worse, the name of Jesus, "King of Kings," as revealed in the book of Revelation (Revelation 19:16) 600 years before mohammed, is "the most awful name in Allah's sight on the Day of Resurrection..." (Sahih al-Bukhari 6205), revealing the undeniable and unmistakable anti-Christ stance. 

For so was it also written long before mohammed was born: "Who is a liar but he that denieth that Jesus is the Christ? He is antichrist, that denieth the Father and the Son" (1 John 2:22). And of the devil, Jesus said, "for he is a liar, and the father of it" (John 8:44).

satan's greatest trick is not only hiding in plain sight, but masquerading as an angel of light (2 Corinthians 11:14).

Muslims, do not keep the name of Jesus far from your lips nor take His name in vain.

"For whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved" (Romans 10:13).
